[x] reply to peer stand up post

•
Kevin,

Your mention of Figma had me look into it spend some extra time checking into it. I've been using Adobe products for a while and my go to app for designing the wire frames for this month's project was going to be illustrator. But actually I been looking for an alternative to AI, even though FS provides students with education licenses for Adobe CC I really have no use for most of the features it provides and find its U/X cumbersome overall. So my research into AI alternatives on Mac lead me to Affinity Designer. I was apprehensive about switching before but after trying it out I haven't found a feature I need it doesn't have that AI does and over it's a much more focused and user friendly product. I look forward to using it for my future vector design needs. – Tommy

•
Holly,

Checking you link on OpenAPI link I am curious as to how/if you plan on implementing custom APIs into your project. Your response might give me some idea as to whether adding something similar to my project this month or in future projects might be beneficial, thanks. – Tommy

